reviews.review_text: We had lunch. We had sushi, ceviche, bacin wrapped shrimp, stuffed with cheese. Everything was flavorful. Our server was very friendly. We didnt wai long for our food.

A visit to La Playita adds a little bit of fiesta sunshine to even the greyest, rainiest Vancouver days. Quality of the seafood is exceptionally high, portions are generous and every dish weve tried has been an explosion of flavour. Staff always have a big smile and warm welcome for you no matter how busy it is. Every dish weve tried here has been great but I particularly recommend the Aguachile Chiltepin if you like spice, and the Torre Hangover to share.

Straight off you can tell they didn t do much to the space they took over, and guess what!? It doesn t matter!! This is 10/10 the best Mexican food I ve ever had outside of Mexico. The ceviche and agua Chile were so outstanding that we stayed and tried 4!! Cannot wait to go back! **the prices here are proper. Some think are high, but this is the price of seafood in Vancouver, and low to eat in a restaurant :)

Great food, high price, average service. Ingredients are fresh. Flavours are good. This is a super busy business, even it s not the peak hours. Food needs time to be served and super busy staff. If you re in a rush, besides waiting to be seated, extra time waiting for the food should be expected.

This place is authentic Mexican Sinaloa style food such an amazing taste and the sushi is so yummm why other places don t do it like this?  JB roll sushi it s a whole thing the  El ranas  balanced and fresh. The ceviches and tostadas I almost try all but not everyone make it to the picture. Chiltepin aguachile and BC tostada and shrimp tacos are a must too. The menus is not that extensive so you can t go wrong. If you re into spicy ask for the chef extra spicy sauce.

We finished every bit of the ceviche!! It was that good! We had the salmon with mango and the shrimp/seafood mix. The servers are friendly. The owner was too nice to that he even lead us to the washroom which is outside by the alley. We will come back to try more from their menu.

I had been trying to find real mexican seafood in Vancouver and couldnt really find anything other than some disappointing ceviches. This place exceeded my expectations, all the seafood is really fresh and the flavours are amazing. Me and my girlfriend loved it, definitely going back.

Are u looking for authentic seafood mexican food? This is the place!!! I am a mexican and is the only mexican restaurant in vancouver that i visit very ofter. The shrimp ceviche and la playita tostada are delicious, the sushi is amazing and huge. I am gonna give a 4 because in the menu they have the photo of the fish tacos with 3 different topics and nowadays they serve the tacos with lettuce and pickle onion in a very small portion . I will suggest remove the photo or add more toppings to the tacos and increase the price.

I have very little experience with Mexican food but this place was absolutely amazing and the service was very friendly! Our server was happy to assist us, too bad we were only visiting Vancouver, otherwise I would come here just for the quesitacos. Definitely recommend this place!

Their seafood ceviches are ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!! It was fresh, tasty and unique in flavour. The portions are huge and great to share with others (if they re in your bubble of course). We had takeout and tried three different ceviches. We loved each one of them so much so that we couldn t decide which one is our favourite because all three were so good. The tostadas were also really good and was awesome to eat with the ceviche. The way they packaged our takeout was really good, clean and efficient. Will definitely come here again!
Their Ceviche was pretty good, Mostly Mexican style and they have plenty of sauce to choose from. Also here you can order a Michelada
Excellent.  Simply the best place Food service !! Staff efficient and kind Absolutely recommended

I ordered via Uber Eats. Got the Ceviche La Playita and was floored! The seafood was so fresh and the sauce was so flavourful. Really excited to try the rest of the menu. Will definitely be back. Delicious!
Ceviche was really good then we had a tuna tostada which was okay. Place is small but comfortable
Great seafood and beer specials! I would recommend to everyone. Had some good heat on the prawns and octopus
As a Mexican we feel really thankful to bring us our authentic flavours from Sinaloa to Vancouver , Congratulations we wish you guys all the best and success.
Exceptional food and service. The ambiance may be minimal but I can t wait to go back. Best ceviche in Vancouver.
The best ceviche, portion and flavor are perfect i love the chiltepin ceviche, definitely worth the prices
Good food with fast and friendly service.
A taste of Mexico in YVR. Not being able to travel recently,  I have missed a good aguachile and La Playita really hit the spot. Delicious!

If you want authentic fish tacos, ceviche and aguachilies this place is a must.  The dishes are fresh, flavorful, colorful and scrumptious. The orchata sprinkled with cinnamon was refreshing. It was like drinking a dessert. The restaurant was clean and casual. The young lady Jessica is kind she took our orders and it was a great experience.  Great service and excellent food.

It is amazing, the most delicious food. I am so Happy every time there. I want to thank the chefs for their great work preparing such exquisite dishes and everyone in general for the good customer service. The mojito, how delicious it is. You will love it.
Don t make my mistake and ask  how spicy is your order

First time here and definitely not Last. Our friends talk about this place a lot, and wow the service was amazing, proffesional and knowledgeable of menu. Our server Isaac was the best with all the recommendations  on our meals and drinks.

I never knew tostadas could be even more amazing but La Playitas were hands down way better than any Ive had before. I just had those and an order of the Playita Ceviche to share with a friend and it was next level. Cant wait to go back to try more of their menu!
I had the matacrudas aguachile and it was amazing!!!! Great job

If you like seafood this northern Mexican restaurant is the best place you can go. Flavour and ingredients are authentic and well served. Enough for solo and for the sharing ones as well. Customer service is kind and always helping. Prices are fair for what you are getting. Worth the visit to try authentic northern Mexican cuisine.

Seriously one of, if not the best, mexican restaurants Ive been to in Vancouver so far. The portions are large and full of flavour not to mention they are decorated beautifully with vibrant colours. The place is small so a reservation would be best to avoid wait times especially on weekend nights but even without one its well worth the wait. The interior in also nice and clean and the staff are very friendly, went here with my boyfriend and will definitely be going back soon!

I had a Taco n a Seafood Tower here. I got a drink recommendation from a server named Horchata, it was so good. Servers here are so caring n friendly. I travel Vancouver from Kitchener, ON. I will recommend it to my friends when they travel here. Thanks for good food and service! :)

BEST ceviche and tostadas ever. You have to try this place. Its an amazing date night meal you can order in or sit inside their cozy place (only a few tables). Had the La Chula and a Tostada de Atun and we devoured it. Huge fresh portions of ceviche with tons of flavour. Couldnt get enough. Recommend +++
The food shows the diversity of the Mexican food, other than  burritos and tacos. The dishes are tasty, but you have to tell how spicy you want it. Excelent service
We ordered tostadas. Everything tasted really fresh. Great combination of flavors in the La Playita and BC tostadas. Would definitely go back to try more food.
Definitely a MUST in Vancouver. 5 starts and above for its delicious food and amazing customer service! Thank you for the extra effort on personally deliver our specific order
Amazing Mexican style seafood!! I order at least 3 times a month and will never get tired of it. Definitely one of my fav places in the city

My Uber driver went crazy on my order and spill all the juice from my meal I called la Playita and they came them selves with a new order straight to my home just to make sure that my order was exactly what it supposed to be I thought it was an awesome gesture from their part plus the taste of the aguachile remind me of home so much it was delicious I highly recommend it my orders was ceviche and aguachile and loved them both me and my wife
So fresh so great! Everything was amazing here and the chef is extremely nice. Definitely recommend sharing plates.
All I had (so far) was the ceviche  la playita  and some of their horchata and both were deadly! Must try this place if you love fresh Mexican seafood ceviches and aguachiles!
Robert and Victoria where such a nice lads! Great service
Very friendly staff and fresh ingredients
Best place in Vancouver for eating seafood! They also have sushi rolls which are delicious! The personnel is very kind and they have a big variety of seafood.
The most delicious ceviche, and you HAVE TO try their rolls.. Such a delightful
Pineapple Express was awesome, almost as good as homemade...
One of the best mexican ceviches not only from Vancouver, but from everywhere. Delicioso!!!
Omg! Tastes like Im in mexico again. Fabulous ceviche! We will be ordering regularly!
Ceviches are so good also the tacos, Gover was great. Give them a try!
I come from Mexico and I can tell this is one of the best aguachiles I have EVER had. It s just unbelievable delicious.
Wow ~ trendy food, good price and friendly staff. Tasty is sooo good.
tremendous. best mexican seafood outside of mexico. horchata
Amazing  sea food. The best place on Vancouver for ceviches
So far the best Mexican restaurant in Vancouver after Mexico itself.
Authentic excellent Mexican ! Delicious   super interesting food
If you live seafood spicy this is your place, so good
Extremely recommended! Everything is fresh and delicious!
Good mexican style seafood! Brings back good memories :)
Real Mexican seafood flavor and seasoning. Great service.
So tasty, so fresh. Delicious! The service is so good
Wow, that was unreal. Best ceviche I have had, period. Truly good.
Best mexican restaurant in Vancouver, I was missing this food for so long.
Ceviche was outstanding.
It was amazing the seafood was fresh and Sinaloa style cousine
Amazing transpoted me to my dear sinaloa...I have been looking for it for a long time.
It is a very comfortable vibe, and it was quite refreshing.
Very good and delicious food.
Best seafood I ve ever had
Best ceviche in Town!
I cant believe how good this place is, 5 stars aren t enough
Best Mexican seafood in Vancouver
Amazing food!!!
So fresh and delicious.
Delicious very yummy thankvyou
Excellent food and service!!!!
Good
Very tasty food,
Great seafood!
Delicious food!
Excellent  place
Delicious as always!!!!

!It was incredible! Warning, the quantities are very large. We ordered several things and we managed to finish them because everything was delicious. The chef was great and explained how each dish should be eaten. There were many sauces and he recommended some and explained which were the most and least spicy and ingredients. And the rest of the waitresses are super attentive. Without a doubt, a place that I recommend.
reviews.review_translated_text: !Fue increible! Aviso, las cantidades son muy grandes. Nosotros pedimos varias cosas y conseguimos acabarlas porque estaba todo delicioso. El chef fue majisimo y nos explico como se debia comer cada plato. Habian muchisimas salsas y nos recomendo algunas y explico cuales eran las mas y menos picantes e ingredientes. Y el resto de camareras super atentas. Sin duda alguna, un lugar que recomiendo.

reviews.review_text: Everything wowwww!! The pineapple, aguache can black tea (it stings when entering but rings when leaving)   Flavor, cordiality, quick service. The shrimp broth lacks a little body to the broth, it is very watery and discolored but what helps it a lot is the seasoning and the size of the shrimp, good for that. What has no name apart from being delicious are the MOMIA shrimp, ufff, you cant miss them.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comments, it is a pleasure for us that our customers are satisfied. We are here to serve you and we hope to have you back soon to serve you again :)
reviews.review_translated_text: Todo wowwww!! La pina, aguache pue te negro ( pica al entrar pero repica al salir)   Sabor cordialidad atencion rapida. El caldo de camaron  falta un poquito de cuerpo al caldillo esta muy aguado y descolorido pero lo que le ayuda bastante es sazon y el tamano de sus camarones ,bien por eso. Lo que no tiene nombre a  parte de buenisimos son los camarones MOMIA ufff no se los pueden perder.
reviews.response_from_owner_translated_text: Muchas gracias por tus comentarios, es un gusto para nosotros que nuestros clientes esten satisfechos. Estamos para servirte y esperamos tenerte pronto de regreso para atenderte nuevamente :)

reviews.review_text: The experience is as if you were visiting a Sinaloan restaurant! Its flavor is first-class, very warm atmosphere and splendid service!
reviews.review_translated_text: La experiencia es como si visitaras un restaurante Sinaloense! Su sabor es de primera, ambiente muy calido y atencion esplendida!

reviews.review_text: Delicious! The closest thing to Mexican seafood and sushi   super fresh and delicious!
reviews.review_translated_text: Delicioso! Lo mas cercano a mariscos mexicanos y sushi   super fresco y rico!

reviews.review_text: My FAVORITE place in Vancouver, I go there every day, its delicious, accessible, and super good vibes. I love it.
reviews.review_translated_text: Mi lugar FAVORITO en Vancouver, por mi fuera, voy diario, es delicioso, accesible, y super buenas vibras. Me encanta.

reviews.review_text: I totally recommend eating here. One of the few places with an authentic flavor of Mexico, especially in the North. Good service. Friendly and delicious food.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your recommendation. :)
reviews.review_translated_text: Totalmente recomiendo comer aqui. De los pocos lugares con autentico sabor a Mexico, especialmente del Norte. Buen servicio. Amables y la comida deliciosa.

reviews.review_text: Nice atmosphere, delicious seafood, oh and they already sell beers  .
reviews.review_translated_text: Agradable ambiente, los mariscos deliciosos, ah y ya venden cervezas  .

reviews.review_text: Very good place I went with my family and friends. Miss Jasmine attended us very friendly, excellent service.
reviews.review_translated_text: Muy buen lugar fui con mi familia y amigos nos atendio la senorita jazmin muy amable excelente servicio.

reviews.review_text: A great discovery, very good ceviches seasoned to perfection. To do without hesitation.
reviews.review_translated_text: Une belle decouverte, de tres bons ceviches releves a souhait. A faire sans hesiter.

reviews.review_text: Delicious food!!!! You cannot miss the tostada la playita and ceviche la playita.
reviews.review_translated_text: Comida deliciosa!!!! No pueden perderse la tostada la playita y ceviche la playita.

reviews.review_text: The place is quite good, a dish that I try, a dish that I like, the food is very tasty, they have a lot of seasoning. Super recommended to eat, drink and stay for a while enjoying the attention and space.
reviews.review_translated_text: El lugar es bastante bueno, platillo que pruebo platillo que me gusta, la comida es muy rica, tienen mucho sazon. Super recomendado para comer, beber y quedarte un rato disfrutando de la atencion y el espacio.

reviews.review_text: Authentic Mexican place where you can try seafood with a true flavor of Mexico, the atmosphere and the music make you feel very comfortable, it is undoubtedly one of the few places that make you feel like you are eating in Mexico.
reviews.review_translated_text: Autentico lugar mexicano en donde puedes probar mariscos con verdadero sabor a Mexico, el ambiente y la musica te hacen sentir muy comodo, sin duda es de los pocos lugares que te hacen sentir que estas comiendo en Mexico.

reviews.review_text: 10/10 very tasty  and very good service
reviews.review_translated_text: 10/10 muy rico  y muy buen servicio

reviews.review_text: Very delicious, you have to be patient because they are very busy but it is worth the wait
reviews.review_translated_text: Muy rico, tienes que ser paciente porque estan muy ocupados pero vale la pena la espera

reviews.review_text: Good seafood, although the menu is limited. The price is fair and they have good service. I expanded the menu with breaded fillet or fried mojarrita.
reviews.review_translated_text: Buenos mariscos, aunque limitado el menu.el precio es el afecuado y y tienrn un buen servicoo.hojala amplie el menu como filete empanizafo o mojarrita frita .

reviews.review_text: The flavor of the dishes is delicious, thanks to the beach team, everything is very delicious. Attention
reviews.review_translated_text: El sabor de los platillos es delicioso, gracias al equipo de la playita, todo esta muy rico. Atencion

reviews.review_text: Excellent seafood food, emphasizing the Mexican restaurant flavor. The only suggestion about the menu is that they add hot molcajete. It would be a very good option for lovers of hot seafood.
reviews.review_translated_text: Exelente comida de mariscos, haciendo incapie al sabor restaurantero mexicano. La unica sugerencia acerca del menu, es que agreguen molcajete caliente. Seria una muy buena opcion, para los amantes de mariscos calientes.

reviews.review_text: You feel the warmth and Mexican flavor, excellent food and better service, they made us very happy, thank you
reviews.review_translated_text: Se siente la calidez y sabor mexicano, excelente comida y mejor servicio, nos hicieron muy felices, gracias

reviews.review_text: Very good ceviche and aguachiles
reviews.review_translated_text: Muy bueno el ceviche y los aguachiles

reviews.review_text: authentic Mexican food, excellent service
reviews.review_translated_text: autentica comida mexicana, excelente servicio

reviews.review_text: Best place in town for mexican prepared seafood. The best place to eat Mexican-style seafood in the city.
Everything is very delicious and fresh, large portions, they serve very well, they speak Spanish. Quite busy
reviews.review_translated_text: Muy rico y fresco todo, porciones grandes, atienden muy bien, hablan espanol. Bastante concurrido

reviews.review_text: Excellent place for Mexican food
reviews.review_translated_text: Excelente lugar para comida mexicana
